The car careered backwards, crossed a busy dual carriage and crashed into a wall, causing the brave officer serious leg injuries.

Donovan admitted assault causing actual bodily harm, aggravated vehicle taking and driving without a licence or insurance while his brother pleaded guilty to aggravated vehicle taking.

But they were spared jail and given suspended prison sentences when they appeared at Wolverhampton Crown Court yesterday.

Donovan, was given a 12-month prison sentence suspended for two years and ordered to carry out 180 hours of unpaid work.

He was also banned from driving for 12 months and ordered to pay £500 compensation to PC Baryana.

