Daniel received a four-month suspended sentence, 120 hours of unpaid work and a 12-month driving ban, and will have to pay £250 compensation.

Recorder Richard Benson QC said he had decided 'with some trepidation' not to send them to prison, adding: 'This was inexcusable and potentially lethal behaviour.

'Some will say I am failing in my duty but they would not have had the benefit of reading the reports I have seen and hearing the mitigation.'

The court heard the brothers took the keys to the car from a home they had broken into at 4am on December 2.

PC Baryana and a colleague responded to the break-in, then spotted the stolen car at a junction 10 minutes later.

